"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been meaning to yelp about Green in BKLYN for some time and I&#39;m sorry I&#39;ve not taken the time sooner.  Every time I walk in I&#39;m greeted with a warm hello and always asked if I need any help.  Although the shop itself is small I&#39;ve never felt overwhelmed by overbearing sales pitches.  The atmosphere is quiet and comfortable and the product offerings are always interesting.<br><br>We all need to buy gifts from time to time and Green in BKLYN is a fantastic place to look, especially if you&#39;re not sure what you&#39;re looking for.  I love the environmental bent, but more importantly the selection is fresh and forward.  It&#39;s the best place in the neighborhood (and maybe beyond) to pick up locally made goods, which I personally appreciate and love to give!<br><br>Nothing makes me feel better than supporting a local business that supports other local businesses that make thoughtful things that I actually want to buy.  The owner has a sharp eye and her finger on the pulse of Brooklyn.  Bravo!",
