"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6s-1W19I7t_ZiU0d5vHhKw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This should be called House of Things You Might or Might Not Need.  During a recent visit, a few items caught my eye.  I was tempted to purchase the following:<br><br>Shake Weights-- as seen on TV, they might give me Michelle Obama-esq toned arms if I shake often and long enough ($9.99 if anyone is interested).<br><br>Leopard print kitchen knives-- for the fashionable kitchen (zebra print also available).<br><br>Sally Hansen Salon Effects stick on nails-- in &#34;Queen of the Jungle&#34;-- a leopard print and &#34;Prep&#39;s Cool&#34;-- an argyle print.  I passed on the nails because I had a hard time trimming them last time.<br><br>Luggage Locator-- supposed to be like a panic button in case you can&#39;t spot your luggage on the conveyer belt.  I never had this problem, because I am very protective of my stuff and know exactly what my bag looks like despite all the other bags looking the same.  Might be useful for someone with limited eyesight.  Might set off TSA alarms though.  I would not play around with things that might beep in your luggage.  Pass.<br><br>Ladies... (and gentlemen in some states)..They have a Husband for Sale set of mugs + remote control.  Only a few left!<br><br>Finally, last but not least, Alex McCord onion chopper and other kitchen items.  Does Alex want us to think that she is the next Martha Stewart?  Doubt JC Penney and Macy&#39;s would fight for exclusive rights to sell her licensed kitchen aids.  If the Alex McCord items are already in Lot Less (haven&#39;t seen any press about the new line even though I read AM New York and Metro religiously), is that the kitchen aid version tantamount to a straight to DVD movie?  (Btw, I&#39;ve also seen Skinny Girl by Bethenny body lotions at Lot Less).<br><br>Do not purchase:<br><br>Crystal Light Peach Bellini drink mix-- even though the big display states than it was seen on the Apprentice with Donald Trump, it has a very chemical taste.  Who ever made this:  you&#39;re fired!<br><br>Stash Mango passion fruit tea-- tastes weird, like poupouri (how the heck do you spell that word?)<br><br>This store is popular, and there is a line at the checkout most of the time.  However,  they have a guy watching and yelling &#34;next customer!&#34; to move the line along.  The cashiers are polite and thank you for your purchases.  Making it easy to give them money for things you might or might not need before your change your mind: capitalism at its best.",
