"reviewcomment":"****This review is for The Bargain Stop HOME store, their furniture outlet next door to the main storefront. <br><br>Right off the bat: there&#39;s stuff stacked from top to bottom and in every nook and cranny of the store. Claustrophobics and clutter-phobics, you may want to take a Xanax upon entering, but I promise - the low prices and lovely service will make it all worth it!<br><br>I had done a lot of shopping around for furniture when I first moved (and tried almost all of the highest rated furniture &#34;outlets&#34; in the neighborhood), but I always found the best prices here. After taking a few trips, I ended up buying frames, a hanging mirror, and a dresser. When I asked about their delivery policy for the dresser, the guys at the store offered to build and deliver it - same day and FREE OF CHARGE! I got it a few hours after I&#39;d paid for it. Hard to beat that!<br><br>It&#39;s hard to know what they&#39;ll have at any one time, so it can be hit or miss. But stop in every few weeks or so, and I guarantee you&#39;ll find something you&#39;ve been looking for - at a great price.",
