"reviewcomment":"I love this store more than life itself.  <br><br>I&#39;ve been here a couple of times already and I can&#39;t even... there&#39;s just no way to describe it other than asking, &#39;What planet did this place drop down from?&#39;  I really think it&#39;s best experienced with a friend, though, for optimal hilarity.  I also think it&#39;s fine to wait a few months before going back because sometimes I&#39;ve gone weeks after a visit and there wasn&#39;t any new stock yet.  Some of the things I&#39;ve purchased:<br><br>- Fake plastic danishes [yes, the food - cheese filled and apricot filled]<br>- Happy Purim gift boxes<br>- Fancy Karen Millen shirts [by the way, you may not know this - because I didn&#39;t the first time I went - but there&#39;s a fitting room at the back of the store near the diapers/housewares - you have to ask an employee to let you in]<br>- A tiny box with a shoe polisher for $.10<br>- Itty bitty miniature bottles of Tabasco sauce and ketchup for $.25<br>- Compact mirror/comb with a smiling potato on the outside<br>- Miniature t-shirt shaped stickers - which, I swear to you, I was actually looking for something similar and couldn&#39;t believe out of all places I found them here<br>- Huge nice purse totes for $7; made good carry-on luggage because they zipped shut [though the strap eventually broke on one, aw]<br><br>Just a few of the many other things I&#39;ve seen but had to regrettably pass on:<br>- A basket of broken saxophones<br>- Throngs of Kira Plastina clothing<br>- Tiny hotel bottle toiletries<br>- Jesus tapestries<br>- Food items you probably never knew existed<br>- VHS tape sets of MTV Jams/Rock/Pop videos<br>- South Park talking plush dolls of the people with butts for faces<br>- Giant Microbes<br><br>Now do you see why this store is indescribable?  <br><br>Most items are very cheap or reasonably priced.  I had to exchange a shirt once for a smaller size [before I knew about the dressing room] and they gave me no problems with that.  Oh and they have plenty of useful home items too but I prefer the useless.",
